# Cursor Rules

## UI Text
- All UI text must be implemented in English.

## JavaScript Common Code
- Common JavaScript functions that can be shared across multiple files should be placed in `src/js/common` directory as separate module files.
- When creating or modifying JavaScript code, check if similar functionality already exists in other files, and if so, extract it to a common module in `src/js/common`.
- Common modules should be named descriptively (e.g., `domain.js` for domain-related utilities, `color.js` for color-related utilities).
- Import common modules using relative paths from the `src/js/common` directory (e.g., `import { functionName } from './common/module-name.js'`).